item.title: ABOUT
item.dc:creator: leeadilling@gmail.com
item.content:encoded:
LEEA ISABELLA PHOTOGRAPHY

I have a great love for life and the people in my life. I am married to the man of my dreams and I am a mother to a beautiful little girl. All things chocolate are high on my priority list, ok all things edible for that matter. I love flowers and french provincial decore, you should see my home (my poor husband). When I grow up I want to be Joanna Gaines. Maybe one day Ill take her family photos! But in the mean time hopefully Ill get to take yours!

a bit about my education...

In 2015 I graduated with a Bachelor of Fine Art in Photography from Brigham Young University - Idaho. For me photography is more than a press of a button, its a way to express and capture some of lifes most exceptional moments. In order to catch those paramount moments for you I learned how to mold and shape the light that is around us all, light is everything. My education in photography has shaped me into the artist I am today and enables me to create photographs that are just as beautiful as in your minds eye.

I look forward to creating with you.

item.title: The Gardner Family
item.dc:creator: leeadilling@gmail.com
item.content:encoded: This adorable family welcome their sweet little daughter in June. They invited me into their home to capture their little bundle just a couple weeks old.

item.title: The Samson Family
item.dc:creator: leeadilling@gmail.com
item.content:encoded: I met Zac & Kym when they were dating back in Hawaii when I was a missionary and it's been years since I've seen them. So needless to say when they asked me if I would do a family/maternity session for them I was overjoyed. They drove all the way from Cheyenne Wyoming down to Denver to have these photos. What a privilege it was to work with you all. I was telling Kym the whole time that she looked like a fertility goddess. I hope you can see why!

item.title: The Simpson Family
item.dc:creator: leeadilling@gmail.com
item.content:encoded: I met Marie by chance on a facebook group. She trusted me on a whim to come to her house and take their traditional yearly photo on their front porch. At the end of their session the girls rand in and got their Halloween costumes on, I couldn't resist snapping a couple shots. I hope you all enjoy this beautiful family!

item.title: The Tolley's
item.dc:creator: leeadilling@gmail.com
item.content:encoded:
Christmas is over and it's time to get caught up on the blog!

This adorable couple recently announced that they are expecting a new addition to their family! I couldn't be more happy for them.

They're going to make wonderful parents. We went over to Cherry Creek State Park and had some fun. Thank you for working with me, it was a pleasure!

item.title: The Coates'
item.dc:creator: leeadilling@gmail.com
item.content:encoded:
This beautiful family reached out to me from a Denver Mom Facebook group Im a part of. It is humbling when working with new clients and

always a bit exciting, I loved being able to capture these special moments in time, I feel it moves much too quickly. And look at their little darling daughter, her smile is just too perfect!

Enjoy, The Coates Family!

item.title: K is ONE
item.dc:creator: leeadilling@gmail.com
item.content:encoded: The Sampson family from a another session referred little "K's" Mom to me for his one year session. They made the trip down from Cheyenne Wyoming for these, so needless to say I wanted these to turn out beautifully! Luckily "K" is really the sweetest little guy, I mean look at those puppy dog eyes. Hope you enjoy looking at them as much as I did taking them!
